I&#39;ve found that adding **amp;** will fix the unmarshalling error. You want it to look like this:

    &lt;address1&gt;Test&amp;amp;amp;Address&lt;/address1&gt;


I think this tells the unmarshaller that the ampersand should be read as a data value (text in this case) instead of an entity identifier. You can see by your errors that it&#39;s attempting to view &quot;Address&quot;, which immediately follows the `&amp;amp;`, as an entity name

